16/06/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The ministry of tourism and the environment introduced an ecological fee Sunday (June 15th) for all motorists in the country.
It ranges from 10 to 150 euros depending on the type and size of their vehicles, explained ministry spokesperson Jelena Paovic.
She added that citizens and companies will pay the fee when registering their vehicles, while foreigners will pay at the border when they enter the country.
(Antena M - 15/06/08;
RTCG - 14/06/08)
